Perhaps it's more appropriate to use a `category` axis rather than a `time` axis.

Or you can workaround on this issue by only show the start and end axis tick. And show the time of each bar with `label`. Like following:

```js
option = {
title: {
        text: 'Date display demo'
    },
    grid: {
        left: '3%',
        right: '4%',
        bottom: '3%',
        containLabel: true
    },
    xAxis: {
        type : 'time',
        splitNumber: 1
    },
    yAxis: {
        type : 'value'
    },
    series: [
        {
            name: 'Left',
            type: 'bar',
            label: {
                normal: {
                    show: true,
                    position: 'bottom',
                    color: '#000',
                    formatter: '01-09\n2018'
                }  
            },
            data:[[new Date(2018, 0, 10), 200]]
        },
        {
            name: 'Right',
            type: 'bar',
            label: {
                normal: {
                    show: true,
                    position: 'bottom',
                    color: '#000',
                    formatter: '0-10\n2018'
                }  
            },
            data:[[new Date(2018, 0, 10), 20]]
        }
    ]
}
```
